﻿# Image BG Remover

## Overview
- Desktop app for background removal with SAM2.1
- Windows 11 target
- CPU inference supported

## Build
1. Create and activate a Python 3.11+ environment.
2. Install runtime dependencies.
3. Install build tools with `pip install -e .[build]`.
4. Run `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\scripts\build_windows.ps1 -Clean`.
5. Output is generated under `dist\ImageBGRemover\`.

## Distribution Layout
PyInstaller one-folder build creates this layout:
- `dist\ImageBGRemover\ImageBGRemover.exe`
- `dist\ImageBGRemover\_internal\models\sam2\...`

The packaged app first looks for `models\sam2` next to the executable.
If that does not exist, it falls back to the bundled `_internal\models\sam2` directory.

## Notes
- If no model is found at startup, the model management dialog opens automatically.
- You can redistribute with bundled models as-is.
- You can also place downloadable models next to the executable under `models\sam2`.
